item.title: v1.10.0
item.content:encoded:
• Enhanced the match-model command with --method to enable part-in-part search
  • Changed the output of matches to include forward and reverse match percentage

item.title: v1.9.16
item.content:encoded:
• Removed the assembly-bom command as it is no longer supported
  • Introduced the folder-tree command
  • Introfuced the create-folder command
  • Enhanced the delete-folder command to enable recursive deletion of sub-folders and their data

item.title: v1.9.15
item.content:encoded: • Implemented automatic token renewal

item.title: v1.9.14
item.content:encoded: • Fixed bug related to upload-many when file names contain multiple dots in the name

item.title: v1.9.13
item.content:encoded: • Updated assembly tree operations

item.title: v1.9.12
item.content:encoded:
• Fixed a bug in match-report where the reference model does not have metadata and the --reference-meta flag is specified

main

item.title: v1.9.11
item.content:encoded: • Added --ignore-errors to match-report

item.title: v1.9.10
item.content:encoded:
• Added --threshold argument to the visual-match command
  • Updated the README.md file

item.title: v1.9.9
item.content:encoded: • Standardized column names to resolve inconsistencies in CSV format

item.title: v1.9.8
item.content:encoded: • Bug fix related to folder names in "models" command

item.title: v1.9.7
item.content:encoded:
• Added "users" command
  • Fixed bug where the owner ID was not shown in CSV format
  • Fixed bug where the folder name was showing as NULL in the output of "models" command

item.title: v1.9.6
item.content:encoded:
• Enhanced the "status" command. The argument (folder) is not optional. When none provided, it will generate status for all folders in the tenant
  • Added "match-all-models" command. It will match all models in all folders at a specified threshold

item.title: v1.9.4
item.content:encoded: • Enhanced the match-report output to show the folder names instead of folder IDs

item.title: v1.9.3
item.content:encoded: • Enhanced the 'match-model' command by adding 'reference-meta' flag to include all metadata from the reference model in the output in addition to the candidate model metadata

item.title: v1.9.2
item.content:encoded: • Enhanced 'image-search' command to enable new multiple image method

item.title: v1.9.1
item.content:encoded: • Enhanced the 'label-inference' command to include 'folder' filter

item.title: v1.9.0
item.content:encoded:
• Added command 'label-inference'
  • Added JT to the list of supported file formats

item.title: v1.8.25
item.content:encoded: • Fixed a bug in match-folder

item.title: v1.8.24
item.content:encoded: • Enhanced the 'match-folder' command. The --folder argument is now optional. If not folder names are provided, it will match all models in all folders in the tenant

item.title: v1.8.23
item.content:encoded: • Enhanced the 'match-folder' command by adding --meta-filter argument

item.title: v1.8.22
item.content:encoded: • Excluded models with "No 3D Data" status from automatic reprocessing

item.title: v1.8.21
item.content:encoded: • Added "upgrade" command to automatically update the executable when new version is available

item.title: v1.8.20
item.content:encoded: • Fixed a bug in the match report which was causing model matches not to be included if an assembly and a model have the same name
